rComments: I was worried going into this class, but Morgan quickly abated my fears. She is clearly passionate about what she is teaching, and makes lectures interesting and engaging. Class participation and peer related activities were encouraged, and she was very clear about what she expected from assignments. Would take a class taught by her again!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Her lectures were interesting, and the classes were fun. I felt like I was actually thinking and learning instead of passively memorizing information. Very available to students and very helpful. However, HEAVY work load. 1- 3 things due every week, which became stressful when other courses began piling up. Hard to do with 4 other credits

Morgan is one of the best. She consistently delivers in lecture on a wide range of topics and is able to intersect a variety of critical approaches. She puts her students first and will go above and beyond to accommodate them, putting as much (or more) into the course as you will. But don't take her classes (I want to make sure I get in first!)

Morgan is amazing, the best prof I've had at UofT, even though she is just a grad student.  She turned 18thc women's writing  (which I expected to be pretty dry) into one of the most interesting topics I've ever studied. If you are able to take a class with her I strongly encourage you tp!

I was just taking this course to obtain the credit and truthfully, she intimidated me with her non-stop lecturing and the volume of reading however, she succeeded when she turned it into the best course of the summer and I actually wanted to be in the class.  Too many professors take the easy way out not Morgan  I pay to be educated  she delivers

She is really nice however she tends to rant a lot about things that don't seem that important. She also always keeps us after time and barely gives us a break.. Attendance is mandatory and she gives us assignments that we have due every class. It's kind of annoying and makes me not want to attend. I have a hard time focusing and have lost interest
